  "texts": [
    "An interesting example is the framework of kernel-based machine learning, which can serve as a unifying framework for learning and preferences modeling, thereby combining algorithmic features such as scalability and robustness through regularization with means for incorporating properties and domain knowledge into the modeling task.",
    "Let us first recall some core concepts of kernel-based machine learning, notably the notion of a kernel.",
    "A function k: X × X -→ R on a nonempty set X is a positive semi-definite kernel on X iff it is symmetric, i.e., k(x, y) = k(y, x) for all x, y ∈ X, and positive semi-definite, i.e., n i=1 n j=1 c i c j k(x i, x j) ≥ 0 for arbitrary n, x 1,.",
    ", x n ∈ X, and c 1,.",
    ", c n ∈ R +."
